Hey NC actors! The UNCSA Second Year film *Of Being and Not Being a Bumn *is now looking for its cast. 

If you're interested in portraying one of our darling bumns, please send your name, age, pronouns, headshot, preferred role, and location to beabumn@gmail.com! Filming dates are April 4th and 5th in Winston-Salem, NC. This is an unpaid project.

items.text:
CASTING CALL for a Short film *RYLIE* 
A Dramatic Sci/Fi short film about a couple through Grief and the Afterlife, funded by the Toronto Arts Council. Paid. Meals included. 

Non-Union

Shooting In Mid-May in Toronto, ON, Canada.

LOGLINE: Glitches in her old footage drag a grieving woman back through the stages of loss, forcing her to confront the remnants of a relationship she can‚Äôt release and the growing gaps in her own story. 

**DAVID: SUPPORTING**

Late 20s / early 30s. Stylish but unshowy. Quiet confidence. A lived-in edge.  Creative, sensitive, observant. Carries traces of a past life: recovery, scars, depth.

Once deeply connected to RYLIE before his tragic accident. Appears both as her boyfriend and as a ghost ‚Äî intimate, restrained, emotionally present rather than overtly ‚Äúspooky.‚Äù

A modern romantic with a subtle punk ethos (attitude, not costume). (2 full days) $250/day

**ROOMMATE: SUPPORTING**

Early‚Äìmid 20s. Social, independent, and perpetually in motion.  juggling plans, group chats. Loves a bit of gossip and the comfort of communal chaos.

Frequently misses the quieter emotional beats in the room, not out of insensitivity but because she assumes everything will sort itself out. Brings warmth, momentum, and gentle comic relief to RYLIE‚Äôs interior world. (1 day) $250/day

**3 TRENDY FRIENDS: 2 FEATURED EXTRAS +1 BIT PART**

18 to mid 20s. all ethnicities / any genders. Three close friends, think subcultures: ravers, bandmates, skaters, goths with 2yk style. A small speaking role will be for one of the friends. Please submit separately or as a group if you can. Individual submissions will be accepted as well. Pay is based on 1 hr of shooting. $100 per person plus meal. Estimated commitment is 3-4 hours.

Please submit self-tapes via Backstage, Actors Access, or through ryliecasting@gmail.com, and please share with anyone who might be interested. thanks!

https://www.backstage.com/casting/rylie-a-scifi-drama-funded-by-tac-3072572/

Held - A Short Film by Jake Nova.
Sometimes what we hold onto, holds us back. 

Excited to share my project; a short film Held by myself. The story explores enotional containment and masking emotions ‚Äî a theme that resonated with me and one I believe needs to be shared more.

This was a self-tape project I created as part of building my acting portfolio. 

I‚Äôm Always looking to grow and connect with representation and collaborators who are looking for talent.

Casting for leading Man/Leading Lady young adult early to mid-20's.
I'm shooting another short vertical demo for two days between now and February 8 (dates TBA) and am looking for two non-union actors with comedic acting chops, to play out the dialogue in this romantic comedy (a few scenes).

Shooting will be in downtown and East Vancouver, there will be a rehearsal day after actors are off-book and then we shoot.

This is a demo, voluntary, for actors reel and directing sample.

If interested, please email me your photo, resume and availability to castingproject604@gmail.com.

**Main Shoot Dates: Feb 14th-16th, 2026 **

**Descriptions: **

**Young Russian Man, early 20s: **Need him available for a day in the week leading up to Feb 14th for a photoshoot. 
Specific date TBD, but we are flexible and willing to work with actor's schedule. 

**Older Russian Woman, 50s-60s: **Needed for photoshoot Feb 16th. 

**Older Russian Man, 40s-60s: **Needed for filming Feb 14th, 15th, photoshoot on the 16th. Non-speaking role, will be playing main character's father. 

**Compensation: **IMDb credit, post-film credit, food provided as well as transport if required**. **

**Location: **Greater Vancouver Area 

**If interested, please send an email to ****duringwinter26@gmail.com ****with any headshots or good pictures of yourself, your reel (if you have one), and stats (height, eye colour, etc). **

** **

Suche f√ºr ein Musikvideo noch eine Mitspielerin.
 
Gedreht wird zu einem etwas rockigeren Song der gut auf die breite Masse passt. 
Thema ist ‚ÄúLippenstift‚Äù Hei√üt - Du bist die sch√∂nste und darfst dich sch√∂n aufbrezeln. 
Ich Idiot stehe daneben und trage deine T√ºten und gebe dir immer eine bestfriend Meinung. 
 
Im Laufe des Songs ziehe ich das ganze aber mehr und mehr ins l√§cherliche und bring dich zum verzweifeln. 
 
Gedreht werden soll das ganze in einem Supermarkt/Drogerie einem Club oder √§hnlichen und einem Modehaus 
( Szenen beim einkaufen und nat√ºrlich vor dem Lippenstift Regal und vor dem Club ) 
Das Video soll etwas ironisch und spa√üig gestaltet werden, Konfetti schie√üen, Feenstaub werfen etc. Am Ende darfst du mir sogar zeigen wie ich selber fachlich Lippenstift auftrage. 
 
Du musst kein Profi sein 
bestenfalls im Alter von 18 ‚Äì 26 
jugendlicher Stil , schlank und am besten blond oder braunhaarig. 
 
Du solltest arrogant und eingebildet schauen k√∂nnen und etwas gestikulieren. 
Viel mehr ist nicht n√∂tig. 
Und dir das nat√ºrlich zutrauen zu drehen auch wenn es Zuschauer gibt. 
 
Drehort: L√ºneburger Umkreis 
Datum folgt wenn die Locations zugesagt haben. 
Vorweg kann nat√ºrlich ein pers√∂nliches treffen stattfinden um alles durchzukaspern. 
 
Als Dankesch√∂n bekommst du einen Gutschein deiner Wahl im Wert von 50‚Ç¨ ein Fotoshooting f√ºrs Coverbild des Songs und den gekauften Lippenstift hahahah. 
Alle entstandenen Aufnahmen/Bilder darfst du nat√ºrlich auch f√ºr eigene Zwecke verwenden.

Auf Wunsch kann ich dir auch schon ein paar Songausschnitte zeigen :)

LACAE Theatre and School Open House is this Saturday from 1-4 PM! Mini-workshops, an Actor's Career Mindset talk, Q&A and pizza! All free with RSVP. 

* [https://www.la-cae.org/event-list](https://www.la-cae.org/event-list) (RSVP here)

**Details: **
Event starts right at 1:00 PM and goes to 4:00 PM. We suggest that you plan on being there the full day to get the most from the programming.
* Address: 11031 Camarillo Street, North Hollywood, CA 91602
* Free Street Parking Available. Give yourself enough time to park and walk over. 
* Our entrance is on the side gate to the left of St. Matthew's Church. (Please note that we are not affiliated with the church.)
* Pizza and drinks will be provided. If you have any dietary restrictions, we suggest that you bring your own snacks. 
* Wear comfortable clothing, shoes you can move in, and bring a water bottle!

LACAE Theatre and School Open House is this Saturday from 1-4 PM! Mini-workshops, an Actor's Career Mindset talk, Q&A and pizza! All free with RSVP. 

* [https://www.la-cae.org/event-list](https://www.la-cae.org/event-list) (RSVP here)

**Details: **
Event starts right at 1:00 PM and goes to 4:00 PM. We suggest that you plan on being there the full day to get the most from the programming.
* Address: 11031 Camarillo Street, North Hollywood, CA 91602
* Free Street Parking Available. Give yourself enough time to park and walk over. 
* Our entrance is on the side gate to the left of St. Matthew's Church. (Please note that we are not affiliated with the church.)
* Pizza and drinks will be provided. If you have any dietary restrictions, we suggest that you bring your own snacks. 
* Wear comfortable clothing, shoes you can move in, and bring a water bottle!

# üé≠ Urgent Casting Call üé≠

Due to illness Stage Ready are seeking to cast the leading double role of Mark Ingestrie/Francis Thornhill in our upcoming production of Sweeney Todd and the String of Pearls at the Chequer Mead Theatre in East Grinstead.

This is an exciting role that is not to line heavy but is integral to the overarching plot of this bold new play adaptation.

This is an Open-Book, Profit Share production.

Playing Age & Gender: 18-25, Male

Rehearsals: Monday & Wednesday Evenings in East Grinstead

Get In & Tech: 23/3

Dress: 24/3

Performaces:

25th March - 7.30pm

26th March - 7.30pm

27th March - 7.30pm

28th March - 2.30pm & 7.30pm

For more info and and audition pack, please email: productions@stageready.co.uk

items.text:
CASTING CALL ‚Äì PAID LEAD ROLE (SHORT FILM)

Hi everyone!

I‚Äôm a film student at the University of Brighton, and I‚Äôm currently casting the lead role in my graduation short film, *Interference*.

William Rayner ‚Äì male, age flexible (playing 45-60)

This is a largely internal role with minimal dialogue. We‚Äôre looking for a grounded, naturalistic performance, subtle, lived-in, and emotionally contained rather than theatrical.

The role involves acting opposite a stop-motion character, which will be added in post-production. On set, stand-ins will be used for eyeline and blocking, and performers will be fully supported throughout the process.

PAY & PRACTICALS:

Paid role (¬£100 per day, 8-hour maximum day with breaks) 

Shoot length: 4‚Äì5 days.

Shoot location: Sussex (Hastings & Lewes).

Dates: Late February / early March (flexible based on your schedule within 21 Feb ‚Äì 29 Mar).

Travel & accommodation fully covered (Airbnb provided).

PRODUCTION INFO:

This is an independent student short film produced as part of my graduation project at the University of Brighton. We plan to submit the finished film to UK and international film festivals.

If this sounds like something you‚Äôd be interested in, feel free to send us an email (interferenceshort@gmail.com), comment or DM, and I‚Äôll send over the full casting package with some more information.

Thanks so much!

Elsie Gregory ‚Äì Writer/Director

items.text:
Most actors stop at what‚Äôs written.
Exceptional actors go further.

Inside the Trinity Acting Method, I teach actors to build behaviour using the
SHOULDA / WOULDA / COULDA system.

SHOULDA ‚Üí The behaviours the script gives you evidence for.
If the writer shows it, describes it, or demands it‚Ä¶ you do it. That‚Äôs your foundation.

WOULDA ‚Üí The behaviours that come from your own life experience in those circumstances.
‚ÄúWhat would I genuinely do here?‚Äù That‚Äôs where truth and individuality enter.

COULDA ‚Üí The brave behaviours that push the moment ‚Äî as long as they still fit the circumstances.
These are the bold, instinctive choices that elevate a performance from good‚Ä¶ to watchable.

Most actors stay in SHOULDA.
Good actors add WOULDA.
Exceptional actors layer in COULDA ‚Äî and that‚Äôs where performances start to feel alive, dangerous, and real.

You‚Äôre not choreographing them.
You‚Äôre programming your subconscious with options ‚Äî so real behaviour can fire instinctively in the moment. That‚Äôs where truth lives.

That‚Äôs screen acting.
That‚Äôs behaviour-led performance.
That‚Äôs the Trinity Acting Method in action.

üîó Train with me ‚Üí linktr.ee/mattzina

#ActingTips #ScreenActing #ActorTraining #ActingTechnique #SelfTapeTips #CharacterWork #ActorMindset #TruthfulActing #BehaviourBased #UKActors #MattZinaActing

items.text:
CASTING CALL ‚Äì VERTICAL MICRODRAMA (Proof of Concept)

I‚Äôm a director developing a vertical microdrama and am currently casting two male roles for a one-day proof of concept shoot in London.
The female lead has now been cast.

This is a performance-led, contemporary take on a classic text, designed for vertical viewing with a strong focus on intimacy and close-up acting.

‚∏ª

ROLE 1 ‚Äì Male (late 20s‚Äìearly 30s)

Black / Mixed-Race
Ideally Scottish (or strong Scottish accent)

A respected, capable figure with quiet authority. Ambitious, thoughtful, and internally conflicted. The performance requires emotional restraint, psychological depth, and the ability to communicate turmoil beneath the surface. This role carries the piece.

‚∏ª

ROLE 2 ‚Äì Male (late 20s‚Äìmid 30s)

Confident, charismatic, and grounded. A natural presence with a sense of moral clarity and self-assurance. The character is steady and perceptive, acting as both ally and counterweight to the lead. Strong screen presence and subtlety essential.

‚∏ª

Tone & Style
Dark, modern, stripped-back. Minimalist locations. Performance over spectacle. Shot specifically for vertical platforms.

Pay
This is currently an unpaid passion project at the proof-of-concept stage.
Once funding is secured, all cast will be back-paid for their work.

‚∏ª

Shoot Details
‚Äì 1 day
‚Äì London

To apply, please DM or comment with:
‚Äì Headshot
‚Äì Showreel (or recent work)
‚Äì Playing age
‚Äì Accent (if applicable)

Shortlisted actors will be contacted with full details.

Act 2 Performing Arts is a newly founded community organisation based in the Peak District.

We create accessible dance and drama workshops for people with various disabilities in SEND schools/groups. These sessions aim to develop the participants expression and self-confidence. 

Alongside this, we are leading musical theatre rehearsals to an amazing cast of local aspiring artists who can use the opportunity to learn new skills that will help within their future careers.

Act 2‚Äôs first production of High School Musical On Stage is taking place in March this year and I would really appreciate it if you could help us by buying tickets.

Any profits will be used to help me fund future musical performances and disability projects within the local community.

Are you an independent filmmaker ready to showcase your work on an international stage? The Cittador International Film Festival (CIFF) in Vienna celebrates inspiration, creativity, and uniqueness in cinema.

Our video ‚ÄúCITTADOR, my CITTADOR! ‚Äì Winged Words‚Äù captures the festival‚Äôs spirit and philosophy ‚Äì highlighting what makes CIFF stand out as a platform for true artistic expression.

Based on the book CITTADOR, my CITTADOR! ‚Äì Winged Words by Ana Bilic, this video reflects the core values that guide the festival‚Äôs film selection: artistic vision, originality, and emotional impact.

Submit your film today and join a global community of storytellers who think differently.

items.text:
## **CASTING CALL: Background Talent (Non-Union)**

**Project:** *Alchemy In Venice* (Indie Feature Film)

**Location:** Venice, CA (On-location)

**Dates:** February 17th ‚Äì February 23rd, 2026

**Rate:** $50/day Stipend + Meal + Credit
**The Project**

*Alchemy In Venice* is a soulful, atmospheric indie feature capturing the vibrant and eclectic spirit of Venice Beach. We are looking for authentic locals and fresh faces to bring our world to life.
**Who We Are Looking For**
* **Adult Men & Women (21+):** All ethnicities, shapes, and styles. We want the true "Venice" vibe‚Äîartists, surfers, techies, tourists, and everyone in between.
* **Bilingual Talent:** Huge plus! (Please specify which languages you speak in your submission).
* **Availability:** Must be local to Los Angeles or able to work as a local hire in Venice.
**Submission Instructions**

Please send the following to **jcj248@gmail.com** with the subject line: **ALCH_Background_[Your Name]**
1. Two recent photos (one headshot/selfie, one full-body look).
2. Your general availability between Feb 17‚Äì23.
3. Any special skills (skating, surfing, playing an instrument, etc.).
4. Confirmation that you are non-union.
## **Perks include:**
* **Professional BTS Stills of you/your character in the scene.**
* **Invitation To The Wrap Party**
* **IMDb Credit**
* **Healthy and Sustainable Crafty **
* **Parking reimbursement (if applicable)**

sharedPost.text:
Liebe Produktionen, Produzenten aber auch liebe Agenturen und Filmschaffende in Deutschland:

+++ Der  erste Gagenkatalog f√ºr Kompars*innen und Kleindarsteller*innen ist seit ein paar Tagen √∂ffentlich! +++

Die darin angegebenen Betr√§ge sind Empfehlungen der Initiative Faire Gagen und beruhen auf den Erfahrungen vieler etablierter Filmschaffender und ihren R√ºckmeldungen an unsere Initiative, als auch auf Gespr√§che unsererseits mit Agenturen und Produktionen. 
 
Dabei werden auch schrittweise gew√§hlte Ziele des Katalogs (z.B. von budget-schw√§cheren Produktionen) zu mehr Fairness und damit auch wieder zu h√∂herer Motivation der Filmschaffenden f√ºhren.

Nachweislich kommt es gerade durch etablierte Filmschaffende zu weniger Problemen beim Buchungsprocedere und ganz besonders am Set, als bei st√§ndig neu gecasteten Menschen, die eben oft ganz andere Beweggr√ºnde haben, wie z.B. "einfach mal dabei sein" und dies auch selbst f√ºr eigentlich nicht mehr Faire Gagen. 

Dazu jedoch nur als Beispiel, die bekanntlich  immer h√∂her steigende Zahl von kurzfristigen Buchungs-Absagen und dabei besonders das Nichterscheinen am Drehort ohne Absage, festgebuchter Kompars*innen. 
Besonders letzteres sehen selbstverst√§ndlich auch wir als ein absolutes "No Go" gegen√ºber unseren Produktionen und Agenturen an.

+++ Eine faire Bezahlung aber auch das schrittweise Umdenken bez√ºglich veralteter Setregeln, oder kaum noch nachvollziebarer Buchungsbeschr√§nkungen (Beispiel Altersgrenzen) wird, verbunden mit  einer h√∂heren Wertsch√§tzung gegen√ºber den Filmschaffenden,  nicht nur zu  einem besseren Arbeitsklima f√ºhren, sondern zwangsl√§ufig auch ein Garant f√ºr direkte  Zeit- und Kosteneinsparungen der Produktionen sein. +++

Auch die Agenturen k√∂nnten so zumindest bei dem f√ºr jede Produktion so wichtigen Faktor "Zeit" profitieren und so noch effizienter und professioneller f√ºr ihre zu betreuenden Produktionen arbeiten.
Tats√§chlich werden nur so beide Seiten mittel- und langfristig provitieren. 
Der leider oft voreilig eingesetzte  Rotstift mancher Produktionen hat bereits viele etablierte und zuverl√§ssige Filmschaffende in den letzten  Jahren zwangsl√§ufig verprellt. 

Daher sehen wir auch ganz allgemein, dass eine Philosophie von "Einsparungen" und "Weiter so" (auf einem sich nicht mehr lohnenden Gagen-Niveau) dem deutschen Film eher schaden als n√ºtzen wird.
Produktionen, die sich eh schon an faire Gagen und Zuschl√§ge halten sind hier nat√ºrlich weniger angesprochen. Sie dienen f√ºr uns jedoch als absolut beispielhaft f√ºr alle anderen, denn sie zeigen uns schon seit vielen Jahren sehr eindrucksvoll, dass Fairness und Wertsch√§tzung eben doch ganz einfach funktioniert.

Initiative Faire Gagen.

Auditioning for drama school can feel confusing especially if you‚Äôve already tried once and been rejected with very little feedback.

I‚Äôm Alaina, based in Surrey, and I work with actors applying to UK drama schools, particularly second- and third-time auditionees who want clarity on what panels are actually looking for and what needs changing before the next cycle.

This isn‚Äôt about doing more for the sake of it or generic coaching. It‚Äôs about understanding the system behind drama school auditions and preparing strategically.

If you‚Äôre local and navigating auditions this year (or supporting someone who is), I‚Äôm happy to answer questions or point you in the right direction.

No pressure just support.

Alaina
Drama School Business Network
Connect@actorsbusinessnetwork.com

items.text:
Hey everyone! 

I‚Äôm in the midst of production for my upcoming horror short ‚ÄúTV From Hell.‚Äù

We are currently looking for someone to play the role of our protagonists mum. This role can be done entirely remotely as her presence is solely from the perspective of a phone call - all we hear is her voice. The role is short but the essentially the emotional core of the film. A relationship that treads the line of motherly love as well being a best friend to our protagonist.

Ideally we‚Äôd like for this to be recorded on a professional mic so if you have access to that would be swell.

I must stress this is an unpaid gig however you‚Äôll be credited on the film as well as be invited to the premiere. Also you‚Äôll be a part of a kickass horror film which is already shaping up nicely. 

Preferred Ages - 40+ (this is not a hard and fast rule) 

Preferred Accent: British 

Please let me know if you‚Äôre interested!

Karth

**CASTING CALL FOR TWITCH LIVE STREAM**

This casting is for talent to appear in a live Twitch stream hosted by well-known streamers. 

**Location: **TBD, Los Angeles, CA

**Pay: **$75/4 hours

**Shoot Date: **Friday, 1/30, from 5 PM to 9 PM

**Looking For: **Men of all ages, races, sexualities 

**More Info:** In this Twitch live stream, our hosts will test their GAYDAR by talking with a group of men and trying to guess if they're gay or straight. The goal is to show that gay doesn't have a specific look, so we'd love to see non-stereotypical representations of what both gay and straight can look like! We are seeking men of all ages, races, and sexualities who want to showcase their fun and unique personalities!

**How to Submit:** Fill out the following Google Form 

[https://forms.gle/T7ruWGqev8txUTCM8](https://forms.gle/T7ruWGqev8txUTCM8)

items.text:
Actors always ask me‚Ä¶
‚ÄúWhat should I be doing daily?‚Äù

So I built a system I use with a select few actors I mentor personally.

It‚Äôs called my FOUR PILLARS:

EVALUATION ‚Äì Where am I right now? Skills, mindset, materials, energy. No ego. Just truth.
INTENTIONS ‚Äì What am I moving toward? Auditions, agents, showreel, visibility, training. Direction creates momentum.
EVALUATION (AGAIN) ‚Äì Are my actions actually matching the goal? Or am I just ‚Äúbeing busy‚Äù? This is where actors level up fast.
GRATITUDE ‚Äì Because desperation repels and confidence attracts. Gratitude keeps you grounded, abundant and sharp.

This is the difference between actors who hope‚Ä¶ and actors who build careers on purpose.

I only go this deep with a small number of actors inside my personal mentoring circle.

üëâ One place has just become available.
Serious enquiries: matt@mzacting.com

More acting tools & training:
üîó linktr.ee/mattzina

#ActorsLife #ActingCareer #ActorMindset #WorkingActor #ActingCoach

message.text:
Actors always ask me‚Ä¶
‚ÄúWhat should I be doing daily?‚Äù

So I built a system I use with a select few actors I mentor personally.

It‚Äôs called my FOUR PILLARS:

EVALUATION ‚Äì Where am I right now? Skills, mindset, materials, energy. No ego. Just truth.
INTENTIONS ‚Äì What am I moving toward? Auditions, agents, showreel, visibility, training. Direction creates momentum.
EVALUATION (AGAIN) ‚Äì Are my actions actually matching the goal? Or am I just ‚Äúbeing busy‚Äù? This is where actors level up fast.
GRATITUDE ‚Äì Because desperation repels and confidence attracts. Gratitude keeps you grounded, abundant and sharp.

This is the difference between actors who hope‚Ä¶ and actors who build careers on purpose.

I only go this deep with a small number of actors inside my personal mentoring circle.

üëâ One place has just become available.
Serious enquiries: matt@mzacting.com

More acting tools & training:
üîó linktr.ee/mattzina

#ActorsLife #ActingCareer #ActorMindset #WorkingActor #ActingCoach

üé¨ CASTING DATABASE ‚Äì JOHANNESBURG & CAPE TOWN üé¨
I‚Äôm building a professional casting database for future film, TV, commercial, and digital projects.

This database is presented directly to production companies, so quality, reliability, and professionalism are essential.

I‚Äôm looking for serious, reliable talent (18+ ONLY) based in Johannesburg or Cape Town.

üìå Who should apply:

‚Ä¢ Models / Actors / Extras

‚Ä¢ 18 years and older only

‚Ä¢ All looks, ages & backgrounds

‚Ä¢ Must be punctual, professional, and dependable

üì∏ PHOTO REQUIREMENTS (VERY IMPORTANT):

‚Ä¢ Clear, good-quality photos only

Title: N/A Proof of Concept 

Genre: Nature Documentary (Reconstruction/Interview Style)

Logline: Survivor recounts his harrowing near-death experience and the loss of a friend during it 

Run Time: Short / Teaser 

Compensation: $100/half-day

Union Status: Non-Union 

Role: 

LEAD MALE (35-45): Lean, athletic, and high-endurance. We need an actor who can deliver a "testimonial" style performance that feels grounded and thoughtful. Someone who can find beauty and even humor in a sideways rainstorm, even when things are at their most grueling.

Filming Location: Denver

Hallo in die Runde!

Wir drehen unseren zweiten Kurzfilm ‚ÄúCry Sam‚Äù und suchen hierf√ºr den passenden Cast.

Insgesamt zu vergeben sind 4 Rollen, davon 

3 m√§nnliche Hauptrollen (Ben, Nick & Frank) sowie
1 m√§nnliche Nebenrolle (Pablo).

Worum geht‚Äôs im Film?
Ben und Nick sitzen in der Klemme. Sie haben den Bank√ºberfall wie geplant durchgezogen aber am vereinbarten Treffpunkt taucht niemand auf. Mit zwei Geiseln an der Backe m√ºssen sie feststellen, 
dass Geld nicht alle ihre Probleme l√∂st.

Die genauen Rollenbeschreibungen, sowie weitere Infos zu unserem Projekt findet ihr im angeh√§ngten PDF.

Voraussichtlicher Drehzeitraum ist die zweite Oktoberwoche 2026.
Drehort ist der Neckar-Odenwaldkreis.

Es handelt sich um ein No-Budget-Projekt, Verpflegung am Set ist vorhanden, leider k√∂nnen wir keine Fahrtkosten und Unterkunft zahlen.

Meldet euch gerne direkt per Nachricht oder auch per Mail an katlenafilm@gmail.com

sharedPost.text:
Call for Entries to the CITTADOR INTERNATIONAL FILM FESTIVAL!

We‚Äôre approaching our first deadline of the season, and we‚Äôre officially calling on filmmakers from around the world to submit their work to the Cittador International Film Festival (CIFF)!

This year is extra special: Cittador IFF celebrates its 5th anniversary - our first milestone ‚Äî and we would love to celebrate it together with you and your films.

Cittador IFF is dedicated to showcasing and awarding outstanding independent cinema based solely on artistic quality. Free from commercial constraints, we celebrate films that are bold, original, imaginative, and inspiring - stories that live beyond the mainstream, regardless of genre, background, age, or filmmaking experience.
Our international jury carefully evaluates every submission. Selected and award-winning films receive a public jury statement, highlighting what makes each work unique and meaningful. Award-winning films will be screened in front of an international audience in the famous CineCenter Cinema in Vienna.

We also empower filmmakers to share their voices: selected filmmakers can submit a written interview to be published in the official festival catalog ‚Äî whether award-winning or not.

Submit now via Filmfreeway, Festhome or TouJiang.

Be part of our journey. Be part of our anniversary.
Submit your film and celebrate independent cinema with CIFF!

https://cittador-iff.com

 #cittadorinternationalfilmfestival #callforentries #filmfestival #cittadoriff

**CASTING SHOUT-OUT ‚Äî FEATURE ARTISTS (60+)**

We‚Äôre seeking two brilliant character actors (playing age 60+) to appear as a playful ‚ÄúRomeo & Juliet‚Äù duo in the spirit of Compo & Nora Batty (Last of the Summer Wine) for a one-day scene in our Yorkshire-based feature film. This cameo will with our main cast, a handful of lines each, and plenty of cheeky northern charm.

**Details**

Roles:** ‚ÄúRomeo‚Äù & ‚ÄúJuliet‚Äù (feature artists, a few lines each)
Vibe:** Warm, witty, gently combative banter, think mismatched soulmates with decades of history, twinkle in the eye and spark in the step
Equity** rates (Feature Artist)
Shoot Window:** **Third week of February** (one day)

**To apply (ASAP):**

* Email kathryn@bad-fox.com with subject: **‚ÄúROMEO/JULIET ‚Äî YOUR NAME ‚Äî 60+‚Äù**
* Include: Spotlight link or CV, headshot(s), short reel (comedy welcome), location/postcode, availability for the **third week of February**
* Please note if you are 1 hour of Bridlington**

* We welcome submissions from all backgrounds and encourage local talent.
* Finalists may be asked for a short self-tape 

This is a joyful, good-humoured day on set, come have a laugh and steal the scene! üé¨

* Email kathryn@bad-fox.com with subject: **‚ÄúROMEO/JULIET ‚Äî YOUR NAME ‚Äî 60+‚Äù**
* Include: Spotlight link or CV, headshot(s), short reel (comedy welcome), location/postcode, availability for the **third week of February**
* Please note if you are 1 hour of Bridlington**

* We welcome submissions from all backgrounds and encourage local talent.
* Finalists may be asked for a short self-tape 

This is a joyful, good-humoured day on set, come have a laugh and steal the scene! üé¨

items.text:
üçí **CASTING CALL: University of Westminster Graduation Short Film (LONDON)**

***CHERRY ON TOP***** ‚Äî Black & surreal comedy-drama with surrealist elements**

Shooting in London between **Feb 14 ‚Äì March 5** (exact dates TBC) 

5 consecutive shoot days

***Cherry on Top*** is a contained, actor-driven short film exploring emotional decay, morality, denial, and social performance through deadpan absurdity, surrealism, and escalating discomfort.

At a carefully orchestrated dinner party, two couples lose their manners as a wine-fuelled confession of infidelity exposes a far more destabilising secret. 

Throughout the film, a cooked duck on the dinner table slowly rots in plain view, completely ignored by the characters.

Performance style: **grounded, restrained, subtext-driven**. Think long silences, polite cruelty, sustained social tension.

**Catherine (Lead)**
Playing age: **30s‚Äì40s**
The dinner party hostess and Hugh‚Äôs wife. Elegant, intelligent, self-righteous, and controlling. Catherine has meticulously curated her life and believes she is emotionally evolved. As the evening unfolds, her composure slowly fractures, revealing unresolved issues and a quietly devious desperation beneath the polish.
A role requiring precision, stillness, restraint, and a slow, unsettling unravel.

**Hugh (Supporting)**
Playing age: **30s‚Äì40s**
Catherine‚Äôs husband. Timid, gentle, and emotionally reserved, Hugh avoids confrontation and retreats into routine and wine. Deeply likeable and sensitive, he is often overshadowed‚Äîuntil his passivity gives way to something unexpectedly dark.
Played with sincerity and understatement, allowing the absurdity to emerge naturally.

**This role includes an intense, scripted makeout scene with Ingrid. An intimacy coordinator will be present.*

**Ingrid (LEAD)**
Playing age: **30s‚Äì40s**
Alec‚Äôs wife. Obsessive, competitive, and emotionally volatile beneath a polished exterior. Preoccupied with youth, validation, and social hierarchy‚Äîespecially in comparison to Catherine. Passive-aggressive, smug, and deeply insecure.
Midway through the film, a private bathroom moment exposes her fragility as she spirals alone with her reflection.
A demanding role rooted in desperation masquerading as confidence.

**This role includes an intense, scripted makeout scene with Hugh. An intimacy coordinator will be present.*

* This is a non-paid final-year University of Westminster production. Food and transport will be provided. Credit and showreel-quality footage guaranteed. The film may be submitted to festivals.

To apply: 

Please DM or email **cherryontop.grad.film@gmail.com **with your showreel (if available) and the role(s) you‚Äôre applying for.

Open to London-based actors or those able to self-travel.

Feel free to share and thank you! üçí

items.text:
Hello, I‚Äôm a Dallas-based filmmaker
by the name Mopsly Man and I‚Äôm preparing my next narrative film and beginning the groundwork toward my first feature.

I have the full production gear and a clear creative direction. What I‚Äôm looking for now are committed collaborators ‚Äî camera, sound, lighting, production ‚Äî people who care about story, discipline, and pushing cinema forward, not just collecting credits.

This is a passion-driven project with real intention and momentum behind it. The goal is to grow together through the process and build something lasting.

If you‚Äôre serious about filmmaking and want to be part of something from the ground up, feel free to comment or reach out directly.

Below you will find a pilot short film I shot, wrote, and produced that was accepted in a Philadelphia film festival

https://youtu.be/jLY9aTxLb-A?si=xyTyqYGTL8-oXEqx

ISO NON-UNION BACKGROUND TALENT FOR ‚Äú*PANKCAKE SKANK*,‚Äù a punk-inflected, surreal short film set in a neon, always-night world where a pancake-thieving outlaw disrupts the lives of everyone she crosses paths with.

SHOOT DATES: February 16-21st

LOCATION: Las Vegas 

We‚Äôre building a sci-fi punk universe and looking for visually striking, unconventional performers with strong character energy. Distinct physical traits, bold style, and unique presence are highly encouraged. All genders, body types, and backgrounds welcome. Queer- and LGBTQ+-friendly set.

**Featured Background (PAID):**

‚Ä¢ **Nuclear Family** ‚Äì Mom & Dad (30‚Äì40s), Daughter & Son (8‚Äì13)

*Shoots Saturday, 2/21.* Must be comfortable with special effects maple syrup on wardrobe/skin. It is a plus if you are a real family willing to work together.

‚Ä¢ **Teenage Girlfriend (18‚Äì29)** ‚Äì *Shoots 2/17 overnight, subject to change.* Must be comfortable with special effects maple syrup.

‚Ä¢ **Teenage Boyfriend (18‚Äì29)** ‚Äì *Shoots 2/17 overnight, subject to change.* Must be comfortable with special effects maple syrup.

‚Ä¢ **Child with Hair (9‚Äì13)** ‚Äì *Shoots 2/17 overnight, subject to change.* Must be comfortable with special effects maple syrup.

‚Ä¢ **Hostess (30‚Äì45)** ‚Äì Directed physical interaction, no dialogue. *Shoots 2/20, tentative.*

‚Ä¢ **Drag Queens** ‚Äì Strong presence and style encouraged. *Shoots 2/16, subject to change.*

**Background (UNPAID):**

‚Ä¢ Diner / Waffle House Patrons (Ages 18‚Äì101)

‚Ä¢ Waiter

‚Ä¢ Line Cook / Staff

‚Ä¢ LGBTQIA+ Bar Patrons

‚Ä¢ Police (25‚Äì40)

Background roles may work one or multiple days between February 16‚Äì21. Availability across these dates is important, though you are not required for all days. All performers will receive screen credit and meals during their work day.

If you‚Äôre interested, please fill out this google form: [https://forms.gle/WoGYUNZX8WGtjqJJA](https://forms.gle/WoGYUNZX8WGtjqJJA) 

If you have any questions please feel free to reach us at **[pancakeskankcasting@gmail.com](mailto:pancakeskankcasting@gmail.com)**.

Thank you!

**CASTING CALL FOR TWITCH LIVE STREAM**

This casting is for talent to appear in a live Twitch stream hosted by well-known streamers. 

**Location: **TBD, Los Angeles, CA

**Pay: **$75/5hours

**Shoot Date: **Friday, 1/30, from 5 PM to 9 PM

**Looking For: **Men of all ages, races, sexualities 

**More Info:** In this Twitch live stream, our hosts will test their GAYDAR by talking with a group of men and trying to guess if they're gay or straight. The goal is to show that gay doesn't have a specific look, so we'd love to see non-stereotypical representations of what both gay and straight can look like! We are seeking men of all ages, races, and sexualities who want to showcase their fun and unique personalities!

**How to Submit:** Fill out the following Google Form 

[https://forms.gle/T7ruWGqev8txUTCM8](https://forms.gle/T7ruWGqev8txUTCM8)
